HEADWORD: Tasset
<hw>Tas"set</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Tasse</er>.]</ety> <def>A defense for the front of the thigh,
consisting of one or more iron plates hanging from the belt on the lower
edge of the corselet.</def><-- same as tasse? -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

